General Atu: Why did you stop the Tarasa invasion at the
worst possible timing? Why did you sign a ceasefire

dobby_dispchara skin 15001 0 0

Queen Caron: I will overlook it this time due to your past
achievements and your friendship with my husband, but there
won't be a second chance.

Senator Pilia: So, you were aware of King Agnos' impending

Senator Pilia: While the military was fixated on Tarasa, and
while the Senate was in chaos due to the king's passing...
Senator Pilia: You're quite the politician, Caron.

dobby_dispchara skin 15008 0 0

Senator Pilia: Wait, General Atu.

General Atu: Don't stop, Pilia. If we cut off this person's

Senator Pilia: Caron, who knows too little about politics,

dobby_dispchara skin 15004 0 0

Queen Caron: However, it seems that I also made mistakes. In

dobby_dispchara skin 15002 0 0

dobby_dispchara skin 15005 0 0

Queen Caron: Or... will General Atu, the eldest brother of

Senator Pilia: Atu, first prince Rex is missing, and Caron

dobby_dispchara clear

Senator Pilia: You and I should be in agreement on wanting

dobby_dispchara skin 0 0 16004
General Atu: ......

Senator Pilia: I despise Caron from the bottom of my heart.
I can't forgive her for taking the place of my deceased
sister.

Senator Pilia: However, we must acknowledge that we have
already suffered a political defeat.
dobby_dispchara clear

Caron's audience with Atu was the moment when he lost
everything. The death of his friend, King Agnos, the dream
of the Tarasa invasion, the final grand stage... It was a
difficult reality to accept, being defeated by a single
woman without a trace of military power.

A feeling of discomfort, as if being bound by intricately
intertwined chains. In the palace that had turned into a den
of demons, there was nothing Atu could do.

Atu entrusted the political struggle surrounding the palace
to Pilia and focused on improving the security within the
empire using military force. Rather than obstructing this
action, Caron actually endorsed it.

Atu considered stepping down from the position of general
several times. However, there was a high possibility that
his successor would be someone under Caron's influence, so
he concluded that it would be better for him to stay.

Unfortunately, this also went according to Caron's plan. As
a result, it will be perceived that General Atu is
supporting Queen Caron, which will solidify Caron's
position.

After the minimum level of public security was restored, Atu
began training his successor. While appearing to freely
travel throughout the empire, he started exerting his
influence over the Caron faction's powerful figures.

I thought I would never have another chance to give my all
as a warrior... But just as I was thinking that, a dragon
appeared, and then the rebellion of Lex. Atu felt a sense of
joy at the anticipation of battling against strong
opponents.

I considered it my duty as the general of the empire, not
just a personal desire, to defeat Prince Lex, who has become
a host for a dragon. There was no joy in it, but rather a
sense of duty and justice.

This is not a battle to defeat the enemy general. It is a
battle to subjugate a wingless dragon. Everything is for the
empire, everything is for the citizens of the empire.

Atu tightly gripped his sword and vowed. To kill the son of
his friend, and the childhood friend he had walked together
with.
